The staff and owner are real nice people. The pizza is delicious and the star of the show is the Sicilian slice. The price is just right, you can go in with a family of four or some friends and spend $20 to buy everybody something which is nice. I'm sure the owner keeps his price point steady too as to keep his customers happy, its one of the major factors that helps him keeps my business, in todays economy we all have to eat at an affordable place and Anthony's is it. I have kids, he makes great pizza at affordable prices, so he will always keep his customers like me happy. I cant say enough good things about the place, its right near the bus stop for easy access if you don't have a car, there open late till 11pm. My grandfather's favorite pizza was Anthony's, hes in heaven now and we miss him so much, and everytime I go to Anthony's l think of my grandfather and how much he loved the pizza, Anthony's has a special place in my heart and the community heart.
